text: Barcinek is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Stara Kamienica, within Jelenia Góra County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. It lies approximately north-east of Stara Kamienica, west of Jelenia Góra, and west of the regional capital Wrocław. The village has a population of 610. ==References== Barcinek
